---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Count Easy - Support"
  description="Get help with Count Easy - Countdown & Days Tracker iOS app."
  ogUrl="https://idlefusion.com/count-easy/support"
>
  <main>
    <section class="section-padding">
      <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-8">Support</h1>

        <div class="text-[var(--text-secondary)] leading-relaxed mb-12">
          <p class="text-lg mb-4">Need help with Count Easy?</p>
          <p>Send us an email at <a href="mailto:support@idlefusion.com?subject=Count%20Easy%20Support%20Request" class="text-[var(--accent-primary)] hover:underline">support@idlefusion.com</a> and we'll get back to you as soon as we can.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-8">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

          <div class="space-y-6">
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">How do I create a countdown?</h3>
              <p class="text-[var(--text-secondary)]">Tap the + button in the app, enter a title, select a date, and choose a color. If you pick a future date, you'll see "days until." If you pick a past date, you'll see "days since."</p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">How do I add widgets to my home screen?</h3>
              <p class="text-[var(--text-secondary)]">Long-press on your home screen, tap the + button in the top corner, search for "Count Easy," and select your preferred widget size. After adding, tap the widget to choose which countdown to display.</p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">How do I add a lock screen widget?</h3>
              <p class="text-[var(--text-secondary)]">Long-press on your lock screen, tap "Customize," select the lock screen, and tap the widget area. Find Count Easy and add a widget to see your countdown at a glance.</p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">What's the difference between "days until" and "days since"?</h3>
              <p class="text-[var(--text-secondary)]">"Days until" counts down to a future date (like a vacation or birthday). "Days since" counts up from a past date (like tracking how long you've maintained a habit or since a milestone).</p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">How do repeating events work?</h3>
              <p class="text-[var(--text-secondary)]">When you create a countdown, you can set it to repeat annually. This is perfect for birthdays and anniversaries â€” the countdown automatically resets to the next year after the date passes.</p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">Can I sync my countdowns between devices?</h3>
              <p class="text-[var(--text-secondary)]">Count Easy currently stores all data locally on your device. There's no cloud sync between devices. This keeps your data private and the app working offline.</p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">What happens if I delete the app?</h3>
              <p class="text-[var(--text-secondary)]">All your countdown data will be deleted. If you have iOS backups enabled, your data may be included in those backups and restored if you reinstall.</p>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-[var(--text-primary)] mb-2">Why aren't my widgets updating?</h3>
              <p class="text-[var(--text-secondary)]">iOS controls when widgets refresh. If a widget seems stuck, try removing and re-adding it. Make sure Low Power Mode isn't limiting background refreshes.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
